# CI/CD Supply Chain

## TR-SEC-009 — CI pipelines run least-privilege and fully pinned

Every CI workflow declares an explicit least-privilege permissions block (default contents: read; broader scopes granted per-job with a comment stating why). Third-party CI actions are pinned to a full commit SHA, not a mutable tag, with the human-readable version in a trailing comment. Runtime dependencies past POC tier are pinned to exact versions so the audited dependency set is the set that runs. Counters MITRE ATT&CK T1195 (Supply Chain Compromise) and limits the blast radius of a compromised workflow token.
